  "title": "Cost Estimator/ Quantity Surveyor (HVAC Industry) #78929",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: HVAC Solutions Provider</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Cost Estimator</strong></li><li>Working Location: MacPherson (near MRT)</li><li>Working Hours: 5 Days. Mon – Fri (8.30am – 5.30pm)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic Salary + AWS</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Analyze blueprints, specifications, and related documents to prepare accurate cost estimates.</li><li>Collaborate with engineering, procurement, and project teams to gather data and validate assumptions.</li><li>Prepare detailed cost breakdowns for materials, labor, equipment, and overhead.</li><li>Monitor market trends and pricing fluctuations to ensure competitive estimates.</li><li>Develop and maintain cost databases and estimation models.</li><li>Present cost reports and pricing strategies to management and clients.</li><li>Support tender submissions and bid proposals.</li><li>Adjust estimates based on scope changes and client feedback.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in Engineering, Quantity Surveying, or related field.</li><li>2-3 years of experience in cost estimation, preferably in HVAC, M&E, or construction sectors.</li><li>Have knowledge with estimation software (e.g., CostX, Bluebeam, Excel).</li><li>Strong analytical and numerical skills.</li><li>Excellent communication and stakeholder management abilities.</li><li>Ability to work independently and meet tight deadlines.</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#78929 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Rachael Lee | EA Reg No.: R2093131</p>",
